\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s boots clicked softly on the stone path as she crossed the campus grounds, the foggy air curling around her like ghostly ribbons. Her scarf was pulled tight around her neck, and she buttoned her coat all the way up, her gloved hands tucked into her sleeves to fend off the creeping cold.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The lamplight from the faculty buildings spilled in golden puddles onto the walkway, but the rest of Edenfield was dim and quiet\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 students tucked away in their dorms or libraries, the hum of campus life reduced to stillness.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She reached the bus stop at the edge of the quad, where the wrought-iron sign swayed slightly in the breeze. The enchanted schedule flickered faintly, glowing with runes that shifted to show }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Aetherell Reach \endash  6 min.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 With a quiet sigh, Madeleine sat down on the bench, the cold seeping through the wooden slats. She leaned back and let her head tilt toward the sky, watching her breath fog in the moonlight. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Her gaze drifted out across the empty road, unfocused.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 But her thoughts didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t stay still for long. They circled back\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 inevitably\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to her conversation with Professor Hudson.\line \line }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Military alchemist.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The words rattled in her thoughts. Professor Hudson\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Gareth Hudson}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 had been a soldier. A Military Alchemist. A man who\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d trained cadets at\~Crownstead Academy, where the kingdom\u8217\'92s most lethal alchemists were forged. How had she never known?}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 No wonder he locks lecture doors at the first bell. No wonder his grading feels like a tribunal.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And his daughter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s breath fogged in the moonlight. If the girl had vanished before ever attending Edenfield, she must\u8217\'92ve been young. Twelve? Thirteen? The age when kids still pressed flowers into books and dreamed of working with gryphons.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Had Hudson searched for her? Had he turned his alchemy toward something darker in his grief?}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Stop.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~She shook her head. She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d volunteered beside him for two years\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 watched him soothe a newborn hippogriff with hands steady as a surgeon\u8217\'92s, heard him mutter corrections to first-years with more patience than they deserved. The man she knew was strict, yes, but not\u8230\'85}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Not what?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A gust of wind hissed through the trees. The lamplights flickered, painting the path ahead in erratic gold.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The nickname some students used for him suddenly made sense, her classmates used to call him }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Sergeant}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 . She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d always assumed it was just for his drillmaster demeanor. Now, she wondered if they\u8217\'92d known more than she did.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Her steps slowed near the bus stop. The wrought-iron sign creaked in the wind, the enchanted schedule flashing\~}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Aetherell Reach \endash  6 min}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She sat heavily on the bench, the cold seeping through her coat.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 How much do we really know about anyone?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Hudson with his military past and missing child. Walther with his too-precise knowledge of tiger anatomy and those\~}{\f2\fs24\b1\i0 surgical scars}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~on his wrists.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Her hand drifted to her satchel, where the sketch of the chimaera lay hidden.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Two men with secrets. Two men who\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92d stared at that drawing like it was a ghost.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The bus loomed in the distance, its windows glowing like a beacon.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Still, something didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t sit right.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 She sat up straighter, her fingers curling against her knees. }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Wait.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Two things clicked. Then three. Then four.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s breath caught in her throat.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Research\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85 deep anatomical knowledge\u8230\'85 access to vulnerable populations\u8230\'85 a strange, cold fascination with a creature that shouldn\u8217\'92t exist\u8230\'85}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Her hand flew to her satchel, as if instinctively checking her sketches were still there.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Her face slowly paled, lips parting slightly as a horrible thought took shape. Not fully formed\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but enough to cast a shadow over everything she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d been trying to ignore.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Could it be?}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 No. No, that\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s insane\u8230\'85}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  she told herself. But her gut didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t agree. Her heart was thudding now, dull and fast beneath her scarf. The pieces didn\u8217\'92t fit perfectly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but they sat too close not to touch.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The wind picked up again, rustling the trees behind the shelter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Madeleine stared ahead, her eyes wide, her breath held.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The bus rolled up in the distance. But she no longer felt the comfort of home awaiting her. Only a hollow, rising dread.}
